                       Station Port Configuration Help           Page 1 of 5
 
      A station port configuration record is one which informs the
      station which drops to poll on each port.  This information
      is cross referenced with the terminal configuration information,
      allowing the station to determine all necessary parameters for
      configuration.
 
      This menu allows station port configuration functions to be performed,
      including: adding, modifying, deleting, and listing station port
      configurations.
 
      Adding A Station Port Configuration Class
      =========================================
      To add a station port configuration to the Distributed Network,
      enter "1" (for Add Station Port), and press return.  The program will
      then prompt for the station number, and then the port number.
      If the class already exists, an error message will be
      displayed, and you will be prompted for station.
 
 
